#Laden und Daten

library(tidyverse)
library(arules)
library(arulesViz)
read_csv("all2.csv")

-- Column specification -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cols(
  ISBN = col_character(),
  `Book-Title` = col_character(),
  `Book-Author` = col_character(),
  `Year-Of-Publication` = col_double(),
  Publisher = col_character(),
  `User-ID` = col_double(),
  `Book-Rating` = col_double(),
  Location = col_character(),
  Age = col_character(),
  n = col_double(),
  country = col_character()
)
all2

#1. Erstellen Sie eine Analyse, bei der nicth die Bcher, sondern die Autoren in den Transaktionen enthalten sind.

i <- split(all2$`Book-Author`, all2$`User-ID`)
txn <- as(i, "transactions")
removing duplicated items in transactions
basket_rules <- apriori(txn, parameter = list(sup = 0.0020, conf = 0.005, minlen=2, target="rules"))
Apriori

myRules_Direct <- as(basket_rules, "data.frame")
basket_rules_hi <- head(basket_rules, by ="lift",100)
head(myRules_Direct, 20)
plot(basket_rules_hi, method="graph", main="Books")
